title: Bug 109350: Output parameter does not display in data set dialog
description: When calling a stored procedure from an Oracle database, the query result is stored in an output parameter as an object. However, when viewing the query result page, no data is returned. The expected result is that the output parameter should be displayed in the edit data set dialog.
OB: The output parameter is not being displayed in the data set dialog when viewing the query result page.
EB: The output parameter should be displayed in the data set dialog when viewing the query result page.
SR: To reproduce the issue: 1. Call a stored procedure from an Oracle database. 2. Check the query result page. The output parameter should not be displayed in the edit data set dialog.
